#!/usr/bin/pseudocode
This is not yet a runnable script

$ sudo apt-get update; apt-get upgrade
$ sudo apt-get install git
$ cd ~
$ git clone git://github.com/AGNUcius/GNUnix.git

$ mv GNUnix/* .
$ mv GNUnix/.* .

Basic Desktop to manage files, processess, packages, power, screen, audio, web
$ sudo apt-get install xinit xterm icewm wdm big-cursor xlockmore pm-utils htop alsa-utils xfe synaptic chromium-browser

$ if (laptop)
$ {
$  sudo apt-get install yacpi wicd-curses wireless-regdb crda iw rfkill
$  sudo rfkill list all
$  sudo pm-powersave
$ }

If using wdm, select "icewm-session" from the "Start WM" button for the first login.

To play audio as non-root
$ sudo adduser USERNAME audio

To capture video as non-root
$ sudo adduser USERNAME video
$ sudo chmod 666 /dev/video0


Extra settings that I use
$ sudo apt-get install emacs p7zip-full dhex
$ sudo mv /usr/bin/icewmbg /usr/bin/icewmbg.off
$ sudo mv /usr/bin/icewmtray /usr/bin/icewmtray.off

Experimental backup to LiveCD
$ mkdir ~/down
$ cd ~/down
$ wget http://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/tux2live/Tux2live/Stable/tux2live-v1.2.0-50.tgz
$ tar xzvf tux2live-v1.2.0-50.tgz
$ cd tux2live
$ pkg.install squashfs-tools genisoimage live-boot live-boot-initramfs-tools
$ pkg.cleanup
$ sudo ./tux2live

See ../README.txt for more info
